      "id": "q6",
      "question": "The MARKET_ENGINE_STATS dict already has cache_hits and cache_misses counters (initialized to 0) but they are never incremented anywhere. Should the new cache logic update these counters, and should they be exposed through the existing GET /v1/markets/{id}/engine-stats endpoint?",
      "category": "codebase",
      "why_it_matters": "These counters are already part of the engine stats contract (T571). If the cache logic doesn't update them, the counters remain dead code. If it does, we need to ensure the semantics match the T571 contract freeze expectations."
    },
